The paper deals with the detection of pulmonary nodules in chest CT imaging using deep learning, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed approach involves modification of ResNet and feature pyramid network, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The paper also discusses the issue of sample imbalance and proposes a patch-based sampling strategy, which is a common problem in machine learning (cs.MS) research. Finally, the paper suggests a better evaluation metric for the detection of pulmonary nodules, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR).
